http://duriansoftware.com/joe/PSA:-avoiding-the-%22ucontext-routines-are-deprecated%22-error-on-Mac-OS-X-Snow-Leopard.html

...the deprecated APIs aren't actually the ones we're using.  They dropped the banhammer on the entire file to keep you from swapping contexts yourself.  Including &lt;sys/ucontext.h&gt; seems like a reasonable solution for what we need -- and people are going to need to get to ucontext from signal handlers for the foreseeable future, so even Apple are unlikely to break this completely.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-10-20T17:35:45.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-20T17:35:45.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
